race.comment: Thin maiden with only a handful of winning chances. SHAYKHLISLAMOVA (8) has placed at three of her seven starts, including first-up at this track over 1300m. She draws low and will likely lead. She will get her chance and might be too good for them here. FOREVER JEUNE (5) comes across the border from an astute Victorian stable and must be respected. The 4kg apprentice boasts an excellent winning strike rate when combining with the stable. If she settles closer up to this trip, she can run well. PIKLEMEGRANMOTHER (10) started huge odds and defied market expectation on debut. This is no harder and she can run top three again. SETHACCHIO (7) and AUSTRAL MISS (4) are both lightly-raced and open to enough improvement that could see them in the minor money.
